kml2svg is a simple script for converting the KML found at: http://www.freemaptools.com/download-uk-postcode-outcode-boundaries.htm into SVG format.  This script will likely need the xpaths tweaking for other KML files as I've not followed any kind of spec, just my nose.

Calculations for converting lon lat cords to x y from: http://blog.procontentanddesign.com/articles/single/171_Converting_latitude-longitude_into_x-y_cordinates_for_images.htm
